

The spiral is the usual “Ulam” spiral that starts with 1 at the origin and then proceeds
right, up, left, down, …  

For any cell its *layer* is  

\[
k=\max\{|x|,|y|\}\qquad(k\ge 0)
\]

and the numbers on layer \(k\) run from  

\[
N_{\text{start}}(k)=(2k-1)^2+1\qquad\text{to}\qquad N_{\text{max}}(k)=(2k+1)^2 .
\]

The coordinates of the first number of a layer are \((k,\,-(k-1))\); the corner
\((k,-k)\) contains the maximum number \((2k+1)^2\).

---

### 1.  locate 2026  

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx 45.0 ,\qquad 
k=\Bigl\lceil\frac{\sqrt{2026}-1}{2}\Bigr\rceil =23 .
\]

Thus \(2026\) is the first number of layer \(23\); its coordinates are  

\[
(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  coordinates of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{array}{c|c}
\text{direction}&(x,y)\\\hline
\text{west}      &(22,-22)\\
\text{east}      &(24,-22)\\
\text{north}     &(23,-21)\\
\text{south}     &(23,-23)\\
\text{NW}        &(22,-21)\\
\text{NE}        &(24,-21)\\
\text{SW}        &(22,-23)\\
\text{SE}        &(24,-23)
\end{array}
\]

---

### 3.  value at each coordinate  

Using the layer formulas:

*For layer 22* (\(k=22\), \(N_{\text{start}}=1850\))  

\[
(22,-22)=2025,\qquad(22,-21)=1850 .
\]

*For layer 23* (\(k=23\), \(N_{\text{start}}=2026\))

\[
\begin{aligned}
(23,-21)&=2026+1=2027,\\
(23,-23)&=2209,\\
(22,-23)&=2026+182=2208 .
\end{aligned}
\]

*For layer 24* (\(k=24\), \(N_{\text{start}}=2210\))

\[
\begin{aligned}
(24,-22)&=2210+1=2211,\\
(24,-21)&=2210+2=2212,\\
(24,-23)&=2210 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 4.  sum of the eight neighbours  

\[
\begin{aligned}
S &=2025+1850+2027+2209+2208+2211+2212+2210\\
  &=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
